Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spread almonds in a shallow baking pan. Bake almonds until golden, about 8 minutes; set aside. In a small bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, dry mustard, Worcestershire, and hot sauce to taste; set aside. Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces. In a large bowl, combine lettuce, turkey, water chestnuts, cheese, and croutons. Add dressing and mix to coat. Sprinkle with toasted almonds and serve immediately. Season to taste with salt and pepper.